div1.p: Territory of Washington County of King
In the district court of the 3rd Judicial District Ty. Holding terms at Seattle in King Co. W T.
Joseph Mifford Pett. vs Wm Cochrane Shff of King Co W. T.
Petition for Writ of Habeas Corpus.
To the Hon Thomas Burke Judge of the said DT CI:

Your petitioner represents to your honor at the Court. That he is wrongfully retrained of his liberty by the above named William Cochrane Shff of King Co W. T. That said William Cochrane as such sheriff wrongfully retrains this petitioner of his liberty, in the County Jail of King Co W. T. in the City of Seattle W. T.

Neat heretofore turned on this morning of Tuesday the 12th day of February A D 1889, the said William Cochrane as such sheriff caused this petitionerto be arrested and underseened in said Jail as aforesaid, and that siad Cochrane in coirsingin said avert and unpiecument, acted without any legal authority; that he had no warrant authority or diuety said arrest abd unpresenneted, and that, in concerning said arrest and imprisonment he was not acting wells this direction or authority of any court or any Judge or any committing may a state

2d - Nuit the cause or priturned for this retraining plaintiff of his liberty is not known to the ptl furhter therer this thiat he believes said Cochrane thus held him in custody an an act by reason of custacies direction recirciet by said
I, Josephy Mufford on my oath say that I am petitioner heard and then heard the foregoing petition read over and the deals and delegations therin containing an Jos L Mufford
Subscribed and sworn to by Josephy Mufford before me and in my presence this Febry 14 1889 J. M. Glasgow.
Notary Public in an for Washington Territory
